# VOXERA 2026 — Deployment Guide, File Cleanup & Suggestions

---

## Part 1: Deployment Guide

### Architecture Overview

Your VOXERA 2026 website is a **split architecture**:

| Component | Technology | What it does |
|-----------|-----------|--------------|
| **Frontend** | Vite + React + Tailwind v4 | SPA served as static files |
| **Backend** | Express + Drizzle ORM | REST API server ([server/index.ts](file:///c:/Users/chara/Downloads/vzzz13/server/index.ts)) |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (Neon) | Cloud-hosted PostgreSQL |
| **Payments** | Razorpay | Payment gateway integration |
| **Email** | Resend | Transactional emails |

---

### Step 1: Environment Variables

Create a [.env](file:///c:/Users/chara/Downloads/vzzz13/.env) file (or set env vars in your hosting platform) with these values:

```env
# Database (Neon PostgreSQL)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host/dbname?sslmode=require

# Auth
JWT_SECRET=<random-64-char-hex-string>
ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH=<bcrypt-hash-of-your-password>

# Email (Resend)
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxx
FROM_EMAIL=VOXERA <noreply@yourdomain.com>
ADMIN_EMAIL=your@email.com

# Razorpay (if using payments)
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_live_xxxx
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=xxxx

# App Config
FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.com
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production
WEBHOOK_SECRET=<random-secret>

# Frontend (used by Vite at build time)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api-domain.com
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Generate a new `JWT_SECRET` with: `node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"`
> Generate a new `ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH` with: `node -e "require('bcryptjs').hash('YOUR_PASSWORD', 12).then(h => console.log(h))"`

---

### Step 2: Database Setup

Your database is already on **Neon** (cloud PostgreSQL). Push your schema:

```bash
# Push schema to the database
npm run db:push

# (Optional) Seed initial data
npm run db:seed
```

---

### Step 3: Local Development

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Terminal 1: Start the Vite dev server (frontend)
npm run dev

# Terminal 2: Start the Express API server (backend)
npm run server
```

- Frontend: `http://localhost:5173`
- Backend API: `http://localhost:3000`
- Vite proxies `/api/*` requests to port 3000 automatically

---

### Step 4: Deployment Options

#### Option A: Vercel (Frontend) + Railway/Render (Backend) — **Recommended**

**Frontend on Vercel:**

1. Push your code to a GitHub repo
2. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) → Import project
3. Set:
   - **Framework**: Vite
   - **Build command**: `npm run build`
   - **Output directory**: `dist`
4. Add environment variable:
   - `VITE_API_BASE_URL` = `https://your-api-server.com`
5. Deploy — Vercel will handle the [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/chara/Downloads/vzzz13/vercel.json) rewrites for SPA routing

**Backend on Railway:**

1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app) → New project → Deploy from GitHub
2. Set root directory to project root
3. Set:
   - **Start command**: `npx tsx server/index.ts`
4. Add all environment variables from Step 1
5. Set `NODE_ENV=production` and `FRONTEND_URL=https://your-vercel-domain.com`

**Backend on Render:**

1. Go to [render.com](https://render.com) → New → Web Service
2. Connect your GitHub repo
3. Set:
   - **Build command**: `npm install`
   - **Start command**: `npx tsx server/index.ts`
4. Add all environment variables

#### Option B: Single Server (VPS/DigitalOcean)

```bash
# On your VPS
git clone your-repo
cd your-repo
npm install
npm run build        # Build the frontend

# Set NODE_ENV=production in .env
# The server will serve static files from dist/ in production mode
npx tsx server/index.ts
```

Use **PM2** for process management:
```bash
npm install -g pm2
pm2 start "npx tsx server/index.ts" --name voxera-api
pm2 save
pm2 startup
```

Use **Nginx** as reverse proxy:
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name yourdomain.com;

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }

    location / {
        root /path/to/your/dist;
        try_files $uri /index.html;
    }
}
```

#### Option C: Docker

Create a `Dockerfile`:
```dockerfile
FROM node:20-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci --production
COPY . .
RUN npm run build
EXPOSE 3000
ENV NODE_ENV=production
CMD ["npx", "tsx", "server/index.ts"]
```

---

### Step 5: Post-Deployment Checklist

- [ ] Verify `https://yourdomain.com` loads the website
- [ ] Verify `https://yourdomain.com/api/health` returns `{ status: "ok" }`
- [ ] Test admin login at `/admin/login`
- [ ] Test event listing at `/events`
- [ ] Verify CORS — `FRONTEND_URL` in backend env must match your actual frontend URL
- [ ] Test contact form submission
- [ ] Test registration flow (if Razorpay is configured)
- [ ] Check that uploaded images work at `/uploads/*`

